ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: yes, especially for the students in our dept, this is a core course
I would recommend it to another fellow student,because it is a useful course for students whose major is chemical engineering.
Yes I would recommend this course to other students, especially for students in Chemical Engineering. It is a fundamental course to understand reaction engineering.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Since this course covered lots of topics, I enlarged my scope a lot after taking it. I also learnt some experimental techniques, which may help me in future research.
It is very helpful to my research.
I was working with the same professor on synthesis of nanotubes. Therefore, this course helped me a lot about since my research was on reacting CO to obtain nanotubes.
